  <div class="row-8-col">
    <div class="card white-text the-crew-card">
      <div class="card_media"></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="row-12-col">
    <div class="card white-text">
      <div class="card_title">
        <h2>Meet the crew</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="card_body bordered">
        <p>
          Captain Mike, an American national, has lived in the Philippines for 13 years. He grew up around boats and
          started serious sailing at the age of 16 in Southern California. He relocated to Hawaii and spent 30 years
          sailing and operating charter boats from there.
        </p>

        <p>
          Mike has sailed the west coast of California, Mexico, the Great Lakes and the east coast of America down to
          the Bahamas. He has a US Coast Guard Merchant Mariners license for 100 ton vessels and lots of great stories
          to share. His love of the sea and sailing will enrich your time aboard Alona Blue which he finished building
          in 2013.
        </p>

        <p>
          First Mate, Jenny, is a native Filipina and is a natural on the water. She is a great cook and very
          knowledgeable in the culture of the Philippines.
        </p>

        <p>
          Your Second Mate is our wonderful Pomeranian, “Foxy” who is 8 years old and loves the sailing life as much as
          we do. She is a delight to all who meet her and will certainly make your time with us extra special.
        </p>

      </div>
    </div>
